<p>Just a quick one today!</p>
<p>I am finding <code>occur</code> extremely useful, from building an index from my emacs init file to searching through org headers to generally just having my <code>isearch</code> all there in a single window.</p>
<figure class="emacs-img"><img src="https://emacs.dyerdwelling.family/ox-hugo/20230503211610-emacs--Isearch-Occur-Advice-Window-Focus.jpg">
</figure>

<p>However I would rather the cursor would jump to the <code>*Occur*</code> buffer when invoked as it just feels a little more natural, so I added the following:</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"><code class="language-elisp" data-lang="elisp"><span style="display:flex;"><span>(advice-add <span style="color:#e6db74">&#39;isearch-occur</span> :after
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>  <span style="color:#f92672">&#39;</span>(lambda (origin <span style="color:#66d9ef">&amp;rest</span> args)
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>     (isearch-exit)
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>     (<span style="color:#a6e22e">select-window</span> (<span style="color:#a6e22e">get-buffer-window</span> <span style="color:#e6db74">&#34;*Occur*&#34;</span>))
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>     (<span style="color:#a6e22e">goto-char</span> (<span style="color:#a6e22e">point-min</span>))
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span>     ))
</span></span></code></pre></div>